Author::::Issa Jagd
DateTime::::2016-03-06T10:52:27Z
1. Straight forward, play to the whistle. Goal stands.2. Taking off your jersey is an offence because you no longer meet kit revulations. If he has a jersey on underneath, it doesn't matter that he took one off. He's still in full kit (regardless of whether a goal has just been scored or otherwise) there is no reason to take action.3. You take control of your game, look the player in the eye and hush him. Inform him that you know what he's trying to do and to take the kick, signal for the penalty to be taken. If he says anything more and is player 21 to kick, you send him off and player 22 is omitted from having to take a kick to even up the numbers. If he's player 22 you make him take the kick regardless. Procedure is that any breach in rules once the kick is signaled to be taken, if the ball goes in, the kick is re-taken, if he misses you then send him off.



